@startuml RepositoryArchitecture_Abstract
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 80
skinparam ranksep 60
skinparam linetype ortho

title Repository Architecture — Ideal Target State (All Phases)

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' PUBLIC SURFACE
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

class Repository <<facade>> #FFFDE7 {
  +save(data, hint?) : void
  +fetch(Query) : ResultSet
  __
  +add_pre_transform(fn)
  +add_post_transform(fn)
}
note top of Repository
  Acquired from a connection string.
  Internally resolves one StorageStrategy.
  User only calls save() / fetch().
  All pipeline complexity is invisible.
end note

class Query <<builder>> #FFFDE7 {
  +select(cols) : self
  +from_table(table) : self
  +where(clause, param) : self
  +limit(n) : self
  +build() : Query
}

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' EXTRACTION — Python data → abstract View  (Phase 0.2 + 0.4)
' hint= path skips auto-detection; no-hint path does exactly one type check.
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

class ExtractionPolicy <<stateless>> #E8F5E9 {
  +{static} extract(data, hint?) : View
}
note right of ExtractionPolicy
  **One** type check — or hint= bypasses it entirely.

  Auto-detect dispatch:
    Arrow / Polars (C Interface) → ArrowView
    Python iterable / Polars fallback → TypedBatchView
    dict / single-row             → RowMap (direct, no View)

  Only code that ever touches py::object.
  Strategies never see Python objects.
end note

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' VIEW — the interchange between extraction and storage  (Phase 0.2)
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

abstract class View <<interface>> #E0F2F1 {
  +{abstract} schema() : Schema
  +{abstract} num_rows() : size_t
}

class ArrowView <<view>> #E0F2F1 {
  RecordBatchReader handle
  --
  Zero-copy via Arrow C Data Interface.
  Native path for Arrow and Polars.
}

class TypedBatchView <<view>> #E0F2F1 {
  TypedColumnBatch batch
  --
  Column-major typed storage.
  Fixed-width columns are SIMD-eligible.
  Variable-width (strings) use scalar path.
}

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' STORAGE — where data lives  (runtime, virtual — one per repo)
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

abstract class StorageStrategy <<interface>> #E8F5E9 {
  +{abstract} capabilities() : Capabilities
  __
  +fetch(query) : ResultSet
  +persist(View, TableSpec)
  +save(key, RowMap)
}
note right of StorageStrategy
  Resolved from connection string (Phase 0.1).
  One concrete instance per Repository.
  Owns all internal pipeline complexity — invisible to caller.

  **Transpose is internal (Phase 0.3):**
  Column→row transposition is not a peer strategy.
  StorageStrategy owns it. Hintable (Simd level)
  but never user-exposed.
end note

class Capabilities <<value>> #E8F5E9 {
  +can_fetch : bool
  +can_persist : bool
  +can_save : bool
}

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' PIPELINE INTERNALS — owned by MssqlStrategy
' (Phases 1–4; invisible to all layers above StorageStrategy)
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

package "Pipeline Internals (MssqlStrategy)" #FFF8E1 {

  class TransposeWorkers <<thread-pool>> #FFF3E0 {
    N threads — non-overlapping row ranges.
    --
    Cache-tiled (B×C tile fits L1 ~32 KB).
    Phase 1: scalar tiled baseline.
    Phase 2: fixed-width cols use AVX2 8×8 kernel;
             strings stay scalar.
    Phase 3: N threads, alignas(64) write buffers,
             GIL released, thread count auto-tuned.
    if constexpr trampoline on Simd level —
    zero per-row overhead, fully inlined.
  }

  class LockFreeQueue <<queue>> #FFF3E0 {
    Bounded depth (controls memory).
    --
    N transpose threads → M writer threads.
    Hides network latency behind CPU work.
    (Phase 4 — pipeline overlap)
  }

  class OdbcConnectionPool <<pool>> #FFF3E0 {
    M pre-opened connections.
    --
    Each writer: acquire → bcp_sendrow loop
    → bcp_done → release.
    TABLOCK hint enables parallel bulk insert
    server-side.
    (Phase 4)
  }

}

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' CACHES & BUFFERS — Phase 5 (owned by MssqlStrategy)
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

class SchemaCache <<cache>> #E3F2FD {
  Persistent across save() calls to same table.
  --
  Caches: column metadata, types, BCP bindings.
  Avoids re-probing SQL Server schema each call.
}

class BufferPool <<pool>> #E3F2FD {
  Thread-local or shared pool of
  alignas(64) transpose buffers.
  --
  Reused across calls — no malloc/free in hot path.
  madvise(MADV_HUGEPAGE) for large (multi-MB) buffers.
}

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' SIMD DISPATCH  (internal to TransposeWorkers, compile-time — Phase 2)
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

enum Simd <<enum>> #FFF3E0 {
  Scalar
  Avx2
  /Neon  (future)/
  /Avx512 (future)/
}
note right of Simd
  Detected **once** at module init
  via `cpu_supports_avx2()`.

  ONE runtime `if` at pipeline entry point.
  Entire pipeline templated on Simd level.
  `if constexpr` compiles away unused branches.
  `static_assert` enforces exhaustive handling —
  adding a new enum value is a compile error
  at every unhandled site.
end note

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' VALUE TYPES
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

together {
  class CellValue <<variant>> #F3E5F5 {
    Null | bool | int64 | double | string
  }

  class RowMap <<alias>> #F3E5F5 {
    map<string, CellValue>
  }

  class ResultSet <<value>> #F3E5F5 {
    +columns : string[]
    +rows : CellValue[][]
  }

  class TypedColumnBatch <<value>> #F3E5F5 {
    +column_names : string[]
    +columns : Column[]{I64|F64|BOOL|STR + null_mask}
    +row_count : size_t
  }
}

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' MEASUREMENT INFRASTRUCTURE (cross-cutting — Phase M)
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

class MeasurementHarness <<cross-cutting>> #ECEFF1 {
  Per-stage timing: extraction, transpose,
  queue-wait, bcp_send, bcp_done — reported separately.
  --
  Hardware counters (perf stat): cache misses,
  IPC, branch mispredictions, memory bandwidth.
  --
  Repeatable benchmark script:
  warm/cold cache, configurable rows × cols × type mix,
  local vs remote DB, N thread sweep.
  --
  Regression gate in CI — alert on >5% regression.
}

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' RELATIONSHIPS
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Repository *-down- "1" StorageStrategy : owns (from conn string)
Repository ..> Query : accepts
Repository ..> ExtractionPolicy : delegates extraction

ExtractionPolicy ..> View : produces
ArrowView -up-|> View
TypedBatchView -up-|> View
TypedBatchView ..> TypedColumnBatch : wraps

StorageStrategy ..> View : consumes via persist()
StorageStrategy ..> Capabilities : declares
StorageStrategy ..> RowMap : single-row save / fetch
StorageStrategy ..> SchemaCache : looks up schema
StorageStrategy ..> BufferPool : acquires transpose buffers
StorageStrategy ..> TransposeWorkers : partitions rows to
TransposeWorkers ..> Simd : dispatches via if constexpr
TransposeWorkers ..> LockFreeQueue : feeds transposed batches
LockFreeQueue ..> OdbcConnectionPool : drained by M writers

Repository ..> ResultSet : returns

MeasurementHarness .. StorageStrategy

@enduml
